ODM leader Raila Odinga's aide Noah Akala was arrested on Wednesday night amid a probe into the attempted extortion of Sh30 million from two Governors. Akala headed NASA's People's Assembly Secretariat and is ODM's Deputy Director of Campaigns. He was arrested in Kilimani area, Nairobi, alongside five people including an Asian. Police sources said they laid a trap for Akala and the others. They said the five people claimed they worked for the EACC. The five reportedly claimed they had EACC files showing the progress of investigations into Governors Cornel Rasanga (Siaya) and Amason Kingi (Kilifi). The sources said the group attempted to extort the Governors of Sh15 million each. The six were taken to Kilimani police station. Click here for the latest political news